item.description:
@dwarfs222 wrote:

[quote=“sk8rdude461, post:8, topic:553051”][quote author=lare69 link=topic=671968.msg4493934#msg4493934 date=1440263532]
Hey man, you should use an IDE. It’ll give you suggestions on how to fix those warnings (they should be fixed)
[/quote]
While correct (especially about the IDE, I recommend anyone use one no matter your skill level), I believe that the warnings can be put off momentarily while the OP learns more about the language.
[hr]
But, please, please do get an IDE ninja, they are a life saver when you get familiar with em.
On wikipedia they have a list of the bigger IDEs: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comparison_of_integrated_development_environments#Java
But the two most used in RSPS is Eclipse and NetBeans. Just know you are not limited to one IDE, you can try em all and pick the one that fits your fancy.[/quote]
^this, I myself use Eclipse and it litterly helps you allot!

item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

ninjaken:

That may be the case but it won’t even run the server when I try and run the compliers/run we’ve gone through the files and all but still nothing

That compiler you showed me was for the client, I can tell because the server doesn’t have non-refactored naming (Class30_Sub whatever).

You didn’t say there was an issue with the server.
You showed us a picture of a compiler with no explanation and asking for help.
I, nor anyone else, can guess what you want help with or what you’re trying to accomplish.
You must explain that to us in the greatest detail you can, including what you’ve tried. That way we can figure out what you’re doing wrong and point you to the right direction.

You need to run the server first, and wait for it to be online, and then run the client.

item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

None of those are errors, they are all warnings.

When you read a compiler, you should read the bottom lines first to know if there are errors or not (In this case, it says there are 15 warnings).

You can ignore them as they shouldn’t affect anything as of right now.
But in the future, the methods may be deprecated or removed.
